<TITLE> BRAC official kidnapped in Rangamati, say police and family </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Rangamati, Feb 10 (bdnews24.com)Police and family members have reported the kidnapping of a BRAC employee at gunpoint from a remote area in Rangamati district. Hemanta Kanti Chakma, an education manager at BRAC's Kaukhali office, was abducted on Feb 6 while returning home from a tour of the NGO's schools in Kutubchhari, relatives said. When contacted by bdnews24.com, Hemanta's wife confirmed the kidnapping, but declined to provide any further details. Md Ashraf Ali, BRAC's regional manager for Rangmati, also confirmed the kidnapping. "It has now been three days since he was abducted, although we only found out about it on Friday night," Ashraf Ali said Saturday. Kaukhali police chief Debashish Chowdhury said police had launched a joint operation with the army to rescue the BRAC official. bdnews2
